# ESP8266 RFID Automatic Door with OLED Display ğŸšªğŸ”

A smart RFID-based automatic door system using **ESP8266 (NodeMCU)** with:
- RFID access control
- Servo motor gate
- Traffic light indicators
- OLED status display (2-line, big font)

This project is ideal for **college projects, demos, and IoT learning**.

---

## ğŸ”§ Hardware Used
- ESP8266 NodeMCU
- MFRC522 RFID Reader
- RFID Cards / Tags
- Servo Motor (SG90 / MG90)
- OLED Display (0.96" SSD1306, I2C)
- Red & Green LEDs
- 220Î© Resistors
- External 5V supply (for servo)

---

## ğŸ”Œ Pin Connections

### RFID (MFRC522)
| RFID Pin | ESP8266 |
|--------|--------|
| SDA | D8 (GPIO15) |
| SCK | D5 (GPIO14) |
| MOSI | D7 (GPIO13) |
| MISO | D6 (GPIO12) |
| RST | D0 (GPIO16) |
| VCC | 3.3V |
| GND | GND |

### Servo Motor
| Servo | ESP8266 |
|-----|--------|
| Signal | D3 (GPIO0) |
| VCC | External 5V |
| GND | GND |

### Traffic LEDs
| LED | ESP8266 |
|----|--------|
| Red | D1 (GPIO5) |
| Green | D2 (GPIO4) |

### OLED Display (SSD1306)
| OLED | ESP8266 |
|----|--------|
| SDA | RX (GPIO3) |
| SCL | TX (GPIO1) |
| VCC | 3.3V |
| GND | GND |

---

## ğŸ–¥ï¸ OLED Display Messages
- SCAN RFID / CARD
- AUTH / SUCCESS
- UNLOCKING / WAIT....
- PROCEED / NOW >>>
- GATE / IS LOCKING
- GATE / LOCKED
- ACCESS / DENIED

---

## âš¡ Power Notes
- RFID & OLED â†’ **3.3V only**
- Servo â†’ **External 5V**
- All grounds must be **common**

---

## â–¶ï¸ How It Works
1. Power ON â†’ OLED shows **SCAN RFID CARD**
2. Scan authorized card â†’ Gate opens
3. Gate stays open for 8 seconds
4. Gate closes with status messages
5. System returns to idle state

